---
title: Miso Peach Salmon with Ginger-Lime Rice & Green Beans
description: Looking for a way to add tons of extra flavor to your meal with almost NO effort? We’ve got two words for you: pan sauce. This one comes together in less than 5 minutes with aromatic fresh ginger and garlic, umami-packed miso sauce concentrate, and sweet peach jam. It’s drizzled all over seared pork chops, then served with fluffy rice and tender green beans. If you find yourself licking the plate clean, we won’t judge.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/669e97b546ae2b14647c3b56-f99a1b7c.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67226d5e7b735aa0739780aa-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/miso-peach-salmon-67226d5e7b735aa0739780aa
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
cuisine: East Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 44 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 270 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger
and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}.
Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Swap in chicken or pork chops for salmon. Cook chicken until cooked through, 4-6 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add salmon and cook
until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer salmon to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Green Beans ==

While salmon cooks, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with
a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Pan Sauce ==

Return pan used for salmon to medium heat. Add a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @garlic{}, and
remaining ginger. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings), @peach jam{1}, and @miso sauce concentrate{1}. Cook,
stirring, until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4) until melted. Stir in a squeeze of
lime juice to taste.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and a pinch of salt if necessary.

Divide rice, salmon, and green beans between plates. Drizzle salmon with sauce and serve with any
remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.